# title = The Farmer and the Snake
# sent_id = perry-176-s1
# text = Γεωρός τις χειμῶνος ὥρᾳ ὄφιν εὑρὼν ὑπὸ κρύους πεπηγότα, τοῦτον ἐλεήσας καὶ λαβὼν ὑπὸ κόλπον ἔθετο.
# parallel_id = lyceum-aesop-p176/s1
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = A certain farmer in wintertime found a snake frozen from the cold, and pitying it he took it and placed it in his bosom.
